text.tspan: Pitta is a passionate determined and methodical soul. With penetrating intellect,
Pitta can make an excellent leader and steward of dynamic innovation. Usually of
medium weight and build, Pitta skin tends to be sensitive or combination with
congestion in the t-zone. Common skin imbalances are: redness, inflammation,
According to Ayurveda, a number of factors determine skin health and youthfulness,
and these include proper moisture balance, effective functioning of the metabolic
mechanisms that coordinate the various chemical and hormonal reactions of the
skin, and efficient circulation of blood, lymph, and nutrients to the different layers of
the skin. The health of the following three types of body tissue are especially
reflected in the skin: nutritional fluid/plasma, blood, and muscle. To be effective, a
skincare regimen has to provide support to all of these areas.
Skincare products should be both cooling and nurturing, with resistance or
protection from the sun. Avoid harsh synthetic cosmetics as they tend to irritate
sensitive Pitta skin types. Less is more for Pitta, simple all-natural formulations
Amalaki Capsules; Pinda Oil (cracked feet/skin); Winsoria Oil (ezcema, psoriasis,
flaky skin); Kesini Hair Oil; Arimedadi Oil (mouth rinse)
Aim for astringent, bitter, and sweet tastes to balance Pitta. Avoid hot, spicy foods,
oily foods. Watch for unripened sour fruits, yogurt, tomatoes and vinegar.
- Cautious with not over indulging in meat particularly red meats
- Cooling spices like fennel, licorice, cardamom, and mint
- Moderate consumption of alchohol, coffee, orange/tomato/pineapple/lemon juices
- Early morning exercise. No exercising middle of day/lunchtime
- Meditation is super beneficial, as Pitta types need to learn to surrender and
not try to strive for control over everyday life. Use ram mantra to open heart
energy to allow more compassion/sweetness and cooling of heating
- Ideal environment is cool and dry
- Daily abhyanga with coconut based oils (self-oil application)
